race.comment: SERGEANT MAJOR (11) has been plying his trade in harder Sydney metropolitan contests and will find this assignment much more to his liking. Sure to be cherry-ripe now fourth run back and will prove tough to hold out. MISS JOELENE (1) resumes here but has a very strong fresh record with four wins and two placings from just six first-up attempts. Expect her to pose a serious challenge. ANEMACORE (12) goes well over this seven-furlong trip with two wins and two placings from five attempts. Include in calculations. NAVYONTHEHIGHWAY (4) strips fitter third-up from the break and only needs some luck from the wide draw to be playing a role in the finish. The well-related WARBY (8) (half to G1 winner Captivant) next in line.
